It contains stimulants known chemically as ephedrine .
Its advocates say it decreases appetite , raises metabolism , improves concentration , burns fat and even enhances sexual performance .
Drugs containing ephedra vulgaris , drug-making chemicals and mental medicines increased notably in 1997 .
The sentiment is shared by many mainstream physicians .
Germany 's Commission E evaluated 380 botanicals , approving 254 as safe and reasonably effective and disapproving 126 as ineffective , unsafe or both .
But do these supplements actually work ?
McGlashan calls Cholestin a dietary supplement .
Several states have banned ephedrine-containing supplements .
